%I A397890 #10 Jul 20 2026 22:02:40
%S A397890 0,1,3,5,8,11,15,19,23,28,33,39,45,51,57,64,71,79,87,95,103,112,121,
%T A397890 130,140,150,160,170,181,192,204,216,228,240,252,264,277,290,304,318,
%U A397890 332,346,361,376,391,406,422,438,454,470,486,503,520,538,556,574,592
%N A397890 Minimum binary length of a standard-order composition with n distinct runs; bit length of A351015(n).
%C A397890 a(n) is the length of the standard binary encoding (A066099) of A351015(n); equivalently, the minimum number of bits over all standard-order compositions having exactly n distinct runs. In that encoding a part v contributes a block 1 0^(v-1), so a run of l copies of v (run type (v,l)) contributes v*l bits; a(n) is the sum of the n smallest values v*l over positive integer pairs (v,l).
%F A397890 a(0) = 0; a(n) = Sum_{j=1..n} A061017(j) for n >= 1.
%F A397890 a(n) - a(n-1) = A061017(n).
%F A397890 If D(q-1) < n <= D(q), where D = A006218 is the divisor summatory function, then a(n) = Sum_{m<q} m*d(m) + q*(n - D(q-1)), with d = A000005.
%F A397890 a(n) ~ n^2/(2*log(n)).
%e A397890 a(2) = 3: the smallest standard-order composition with 2 distinct runs is (2,1) = 5 = 101_2, of length 3.
%o A397890 (Python)
%o A397890 def A_length(n):
%o A397890     if n == 0: return 0
%o A397890     q = 1
%o A397890     while sum(q//v for v in range(1, q+1)) < n: q += 1
%o A397890     forced = [v*l for v in range(1, q+1) for l in range(1, q+1) if v*l < q]
%o A397890     return sum(forced) + q*(n - len(forced))
%o A397890 print([A_length(n) for n in range(60)])
%Y A397890 Cf. A351015, A061017, A000005, A006218, A066099.
%K A397890 nonn,new
%O A397890 0,3
